| No database persistence — in-memory mutable state | **Critical** | Require remediation plan with timeline as LOI condition; validate against production deployment architecture |
| No authentication or authorization on any endpoint | **Critical** | Obtain architecture documentation for auth system; if none exists at platform level, require remediation before close |
| Incomplete POST handler returning false success | **Critical** | Full audit of stub/TODO endpoints across codebase; assess customer-impact scope |
| SOC 2 Type II claims inconsistent with code evidence | **Critical** | Obtain full audit report including scope; engage independent auditor to re-verify controls |
| Secrets directory potentially in source repository | **High** | Immediate audit of `secrets/` directory; rotate any exposed credentials; review git history |
| JSON injection via string interpolation | **High** | Adopt type-safe JSON library; audit all serialization/deserialization code |
| No transport security evidence | **High** | Obtain TLS configuration documentation; verify encryption in transit for all customer-facing endpoints |
| Financial services customers vs. observed security posture | **High** | Conduct targeted review of customer-facing pipeline components before close |
| Java-to-Rust rewrite integration risk | **High** | Require completion milestone plan; assess API compatibility strategy; factor into integration timeline |
